 Here is a simple JavaScript function that calculates the greatest common divisor (GCD) of two numbers using Euclidean algorithm:

```javascript
function gcd(x, y) {
    if (!y) return x;
    return gcd(y, x % y);
}
```

This function works by repeatedly subtracting the smaller number from the larger one until the smaller number becomes zero. The last non-zero value is the GCD.

You can use this function in your `fofx` function like so:

```javascript
function fofx(x, banana) {
    return gcd(x, banana);
}
